imultaneously based on Git worktree isolation, handling different tasks like frontend components, backend APIs, and test cases in parallel\n\n### **Additional Features from Recent Updates**\n\n- **Built-in Composer Model** - Cursor's proprietary model offering 4x faster generation speed\n- **Multi-file Editing** - Natural language requests can modify multiple files simultaneously\n- **Agent Mode & Yolo Mode** - For intelligent command execution and parallel task processing\n- **Local Model Deployment Support** - For privacy and speed\n- **Code Traceability & AI Generation Marking** - For team collaboration and quality control\n\n### **Latest Version (v2.4.21)**\n- Last updated: January 29, 2026\n- File size: ~184 MB\n- Built-in GPT and Claude models\n- Enhanced context prediction and error detection\n\n### **Pricing Notes**\n- Pro version: $16/month (60% more expensive than GitHub Copilot)\n- Free version limited to 25 credits (typically lasts 2-3 days for professional developers)\n\nThe February 2026 updates focus heavily on **multi-agent collaboration**, **background task automation**, and **enhanced project planning capabilities**, positioning Cursor as one of the leading AI-native IDEs alongside Claude Code according to 2026 developer surveys.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
