on\nbrew upgrade gemini-cli\n\n# Check version\ngemini -v\n\n# Enable Preview Features\n/settings\n# Enable \"Preview Features\" and save\n\n# Switch to Gemini 3\n/model\n# Select \"Auto (Gemini 3)\"\n```\n\n### **Previous Updates**\n\n**V0.1.13 (July 2025)**:\n- Cancel operation prompts\n- Confirmation shortcuts using number keys\n- Cognitive loop detection and mitigation\n- MCP server management\n- Default authentication settings\n- Proxy support via --proxy flag\n- Terminal line continuation support\n\n**July 2025 Updates** (85 PRs merged by 51 contributors):\n- Audio/video content processing\n- Enhanced Markdown file handling\n- Nested import support via @ symbol\n- Table rendering improvements\n\n### **Key Features**:\n- Weekly preview releases (Tuesdays at UTC 2359)\n- Weekly stable releases (Tuesdays at UTC 2000)\n- Daily nightly builds\n- Available via npm, Homebrew, and direct download\n\n### **2026 Context**:\n- Gemini CLI integrates with Gemini 3 Pro (described as the strongest model as of January 2026)\n- Google has announced that Google Assistant will be fully replaced by Gemini in March 2026\n\nThe tool is actively maintained with weekly release cadence and continues to add features for developers working with Google's Gemini AI models directly from the command line.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
