texts\n- **Agent Type Specification** - Skills can specify which agent type to execute using the `agent` field\n- **Language Settings** - Configure Claude's response language (e.g., `language: \"japanese\"`)\n- **Git Ignore Control** - Added `respectGitignore` in settings.json to control @ mention file selector behavior\n- **Demo Mode** - New `IS_DEMO` environment variable to hide email and organization info for screen recording\n- **Remote Session Commands** - `/teleport` and `/remote-env` slash commands for claude.ai subscribers to recover and configure remote sessions\n- **Disable Specific Agents** - Support for disabling specific agents using `Task(AgentName)` syntax in settings.json or CLI flags\n- **Hooks Support** - PreToolUse, PostToolUse, and Stop hooks in agent, skill, and slash command frontmatter\n\n**Vim Motion Enhancements:**\n- Enhanced Vim actions including `;` and `,` to repeat f/F/t/T actions\n- `yy` and `Y` for yanking, `p` and `P` for pasting\n- Text objects support (iw, aw, iW, aW, i\", a, i', a', i(, a(, i[, a[, i{ , a{)\n- `>>` and `<<` for indent/unindent, `J` for joining lines\n\n### **Remote Control Feature (February 2026)**\n- New **Remote Control** feature with **Mobile Session Handoff** capabilities\n- Enables seamless session handoffs for enhanced team collaboration\n- Allows real-time code reviews or edits from anywhere\n\n### **Version Evolution:**\n- 2.0.75-2.0.76: Transition versions\n- 2.1.0: \"Backward-compatible feature enhancement\" version\n- 2.1.1: Quick hotfix version\n\n### **Upgrade Commands:**\n```bash\nnpm update -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code\n# or specific version:\nnpm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code@2.1.1\n```\n\nTo check your version: `claude --version`\n\nThe 2026 updates show Claude Code evolving from a pure CLI tool to a more mature development platform with better models, smoother interactions, and a more open ecosystem.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
