d plans to release **multiple Codex-related products** over the following month\n- The first product was scheduled to launch the following week\n- Codex is positioned as an \"AI Software Engineer\" - a system integrating models, tools, and workflows\n- Technical blog post detailed Codex CLI's core mechanism: **\"Agent Loop\"** - a closed-loop system combining command parsing, model reasoning, and tool calling for automated programming interactions\n\n### Major Updates in 2026\n\n**February 3, 2026**\n- OpenAI officially launched a **standalone macOS application** for Codex\n- Provides developers with an AI agent-based intelligent programming collaboration environment\n\n**Early 2026 (February timeframe)**\n- New Codex based on **GPT-5.2-Codex model**\n- **40% improvement in inference speed**\n- Supports **400,000 token input** and **50+ programming languages**\n- Integrated **MCP protocol** and \"Work Tree\" mechanism\n- Enables task distribution and collaboration for UI design, backend architecture, and bug scanning\n- Supports multi-agent parallel processing and automated workflow execution\n\n### Codex CLI Specific Details\n\n**Installation & Usage:**\n- Command: `npm install -g @openai/codex`\n- Runs entirely in the terminal - no context switching required\n- Supports multi-modal input (text, code snippets, images, charts)\n- Rich approval workflow with three modes:\n  - **Suggestion mode**: View diffs and approve changes individually\n  - **Auto-edit**: Automatically apply changes with minimal confirmation\n  - **Fully automatic**: Allow Codex to autonomously execute a series of changes\n\n**Community Growth:**\n- As of early 2026, Codex CLI has over **59,000 stars** on GitHub\n- Hundreds of releases indicating active development\n\n**Updates:**\n- Update command: `npm update -g @openai/codex`\n- Or reinstall latest version: `npm install -g @openai/codex@latest`\n\n### Historical Context\n\n- **April 2025**: OpenAI launched the open-source local tool Codex CLI\