ow to Use:\n1. Ensure Claude Code is updated to the latest version (run `claude update`)\n2. Start or enter an existing Claude Code session in your terminal\n3. Type `/remote-control` or the shorthand `/rc` \n4. Scan the generated QR code with your mobile device\n5. Connect through the Claude mobile app or browser\n\n### Technical Details:\n- Generates unique session links and QR codes for secure connections\n- Works with IDE-integrated terminals (VS Code, iTerm2, etc.)\n- Supports SSH and tmux sessions\n- Available for Claude Max subscribers\n\n### Related Developments:\n- The feature is part of Claude Code v2.1.0+ updates\n- Includes other enhancements like skill hot-reloading, Vim improvements, and teleport commands\n- Integrates with the broader trend of \"agentic execution\" in AI coding tools for 2026\n\n**Note**: While I searched for Reddit-specific discussions, the results primarily came from Chinese tech news sites and documentation. The feature appears to be a significant update in the AI coding assistant space, emphasizing mobility and seamless workflow continuation.\n\nWould you like me to search for more specific information about this feature or look for Reddit discussions in particular?\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."
